# Astro Site Rules

- Keep the site a static Astro app.
- Put page markup in `src/pages/` and shared shell/global styles in `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`.
- Keep the UI dense, restrained, and scannable like a technical index.
- Use existing CSS variables and component patterns before adding new styling systems.
- Avoid decorative-heavy sections, oversized marketing layouts, and UI that obscures the catalog.
- Run `npm run build` after UI changes.
